OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FA daytime nap is good for  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fthe brain                  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Regularly finding time for a little    
OL,6, snooze is good for our brain and helps 
OL,7, keep it bigger for longer, say         
OL,8, University College London researchers. 
OL,10,FThe team showed nappers' brains were 15
OL,11,Fcubic centimetres (0.9 cubic inches)   
OL,12,Flarger - equivalent to delaying ageing 
OL,13,Fby between three and six years.        
OL,15,FHowever, the scientists recommend      
OL,16,Fkeeping naps to less than half an hour.
OL,18,FBut they said a daytime sleep was hard 
OL,19,Fin many careers, with work culture     
OL,20,Foften frowning on the practice.        
